WEBVTT

00:02.114 --> 00:03.365
<i>So here's
what you missed on Glee:</i>

00:03.432 --> 00:04.599
<i>Tina dumped Artie
for Mike Chang.</i>

00:07.436 --> 00:08.987
<i>in the shower.
And we'd like to talk
to you about Glee Club.</i>

00:09.071 --> 00:09.871
<i>Finn thought Kurt was trying
to look at him in the shower,</i>

00:09.939 --> 00:11.373
<i>so he called him a name</i>

00:11.440 --> 00:13.074
<i>which totally got him
chewed out by Kurt's dad.</i>

00:13.125 --> 00:14.493
<i>Maybe everyone should
just start taking baths.</i>

00:14.577 --> 00:15.377
<i>And that's what you missed
on Glee!</i>

00:18.047 --> 00:18.914
(bell ringing)

00:20.500 --> 00:23.552
All right, let's, uh,
let's gather round.

00:23.619 --> 00:25.887
Sorry I'm late, guys.

00:25.955 --> 00:27.121
I was with Principal Figgins.

00:28.674 --> 00:31.259
Bad news, guys.
Puckerman's in Juvvie.

00:31.327 --> 00:33.228
It really was just
a matter of time.

00:33.295 --> 00:34.312
What did he do?

00:34.397 --> 00:35.797
He drove his mom's Volvo through

00:35.865 --> 00:37.065
the front of
a convenience store,

00:37.133 --> 00:38.800
and drove off with the ATM.

00:38.851 --> 00:40.151
(laughter)

00:40.236 --> 00:41.486
A-A-And when is he getting out?

00:41.571 --> 00:42.771
Unknown.

00:42.822 --> 00:44.239
He might be the mbest
person on this planet,

00:44.306 --> 00:45.106
and that's
coming from me.

00:45.157 --> 00:47.225
Guys! Let's have some sympathy.

00:47.293 --> 00:48.860
For a guy who put his
needs before the team's?

00:48.945 --> 00:50.946
We need his voice, and his
bad-boy stage presence.

00:50.997 --> 00:53.665
We can't look at this
as, as a crisis.

00:53.749 --> 00:55.033
It's an opportunity.

00:55.117 --> 00:56.484
For what?

00:56.552 --> 00:57.986
Further embarrassment
and humiliation?

00:58.037 --> 01:02.090
For welcoming our new member...
Sam Evans!

01:02.157 --> 01:04.426
There he is.
How's it going?

01:04.492 --> 01:05.994
Hey, everybody.
I'm Sam.

01:06.045 --> 01:08.930
Sam... I am.

01:08.998 --> 01:10.465
And I don't like
green eggs and ham.

01:10.516 --> 01:13.501
Oh, wow.
He has no game.

01:13.553 --> 01:15.220
Okay! This is
gonna be great.

01:15.304 --> 01:16.688
You're not going to
regret joining, Sam.

01:16.772 --> 01:17.722
Oh, good.

01:17.807 --> 01:19.007
Sam, you sit right here.

01:19.058 --> 01:20.358
WILL: All right!
Question for the group.

01:20.443 --> 01:22.861
What's a duet?

01:22.945 --> 01:24.613
A blanket.

01:24.680 --> 01:27.365
A duet is when two voices
join to become one.

01:27.450 --> 01:31.185
WILL: Great duets are like
a great marriage.

01:31.237 --> 01:32.487
The singers complement
each other,

01:32.538 --> 01:33.855
push each other to be better.

01:33.906 --> 01:35.240
Now, some people...

01:35.324 --> 01:37.459
Psst! He's on team gay.

01:37.526 --> 01:39.127
No straight boy
dyes his hair

01:39.194 --> 01:41.580
to look like Linda
Evangelista circa 1993.

01:41.647 --> 01:43.999
You're crazy,
circa 2010.

01:44.050 --> 01:45.199
WILL:
And that is what

01:45.251 --> 01:46.885
duets are all about.

01:46.969 --> 01:50.038
So, this week I want you
to pair up and sing a duet.

01:50.089 --> 01:52.140
And since you guys all
seemed to love our little

01:52.207 --> 01:56.711
"Defying Gravity" diva-off,
I'm making this a competition.

01:56.762 --> 01:58.313
What's the winner get?

01:58.381 --> 02:00.381
Dinner for two, on me...

02:00.433 --> 02:02.400
at Breadstix.

02:02.485 --> 02:03.885
(all gasping)
Breadstix!

02:03.936 --> 02:08.740
(everyone
chattering excitedly)

02:08.824 --> 02:10.108
Who you gonna
sing with, Kurt?

02:15.948 --> 02:17.616
<font color="#ffff00">Captioning sponsored by</font>
<font color="#ffff00">20TH CENTURY FOX</font>

02:17.683 --> 02:18.617
<font color="#ffff00">and FORD. Drive One.</font>

02:18.684 --> 02:20.368
(bell ringing)

02:22.455 --> 02:24.255
Hi. I'm Kurt Hummel.

02:24.340 --> 02:25.707
Hey.

02:25.758 --> 02:27.759
I just wanted to personally
welcome you to the glee club.

02:27.843 --> 02:30.045
Thanks.

02:30.096 --> 02:31.579
Just tell me.

02:33.749 --> 02:35.850
Look... maybe at
your old school,

02:35.918 --> 02:37.469
you could get away
with the whole

02:37.553 --> 02:39.354
"I just stayed in the sun
all summer" excuse,

02:39.421 --> 02:41.690
but I have three gifts:
my voice,

02:41.757 --> 02:43.642
my ability to spot trends
in men's fashion,

02:43.726 --> 02:46.695
and my ability to know when
it comes from a bottle.

02:46.762 --> 02:48.330
I don't dye my hair, dude.

02:48.397 --> 02:49.230
Yes, you do.

02:49.281 --> 02:50.264
But it's just between friends.

02:50.316 --> 02:51.800
That's not natural.

02:51.867 --> 02:53.268
I'm gonna... go...

02:53.336 --> 02:55.987
'cause you're kinda
freaking me out.

02:56.072 --> 02:57.455
Wait, wait.

02:57.540 --> 02:58.990
Maybe my instincts
were a little off.

02:59.075 --> 03:00.608
Let me make it up to you.

03:00.660 --> 03:02.377
Team up with me for
the duet competition.

03:02.444 --> 03:03.795
Listen, unless you
team up with Rachel,

03:03.879 --> 03:05.463
I am your best
bet at winning.

03:05.548 --> 03:07.966
Aren't duets supposed to be
between, like, a girl and a guy?

03:08.050 --> 03:10.418
Well, Gene Kelly and Donald
O'Connor would protest.

03:10.469 --> 03:11.553
"Make'em Laugh"?

03:11.620 --> 03:12.721
Sorry.

03:12.788 --> 03:14.589
<i>Singin' in the Rain.
1952.</i>

03:14.640 --> 03:16.391
Nothing. Okay, maybe
you are straight.

03:16.458 --> 03:18.309
What?
Nothing. Listen, rent it.

03:18.394 --> 03:20.011
and then look up the menu
for Breadstix online,

03:20.096 --> 03:21.513
and call me, because
we are gonna win this.

03:21.597 --> 03:23.982
(bell ringing)

03:25.000 --> 03:31.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:32.141 --> 03:34.609
BRITTANY:
I love your sweet lady kisses.

03:34.660 --> 03:36.244
Mm-hmm.

03:36.311 --> 03:38.863
It's a nice break from
all that scissoring.

03:38.948 --> 03:40.865
We should do a
duet together.

03:40.950 --> 03:43.702
We should sing Melissa
Ethridge's "Come To My Window."

03:43.786 --> 03:45.120
First of all?

03:45.171 --> 03:46.554
There's a lot of
talking going on,

03:46.622 --> 03:48.006
and I wants ta
get my mack on.

03:48.090 --> 03:49.958
Well... I don't know,
I just... I think we just...

03:50.009 --> 03:51.492
Okay, second of all?

03:51.544 --> 03:53.962
I'm not making out with you
because I'm in love with you

03:54.013 --> 03:55.847
and want to sing about
making lady babies.

03:55.915 --> 03:58.016
I'm only here because Puck's
been in the slammer

03:58.100 --> 03:59.701
for about 12 hours now,
and I'm like a lizard.

03:59.769 --> 04:02.554
I need something warm beneath
me, or I can't digest my food.

04:02.638 --> 04:05.407
But who are you going
to sing a duet with?

04:05.474 --> 04:06.941
(bell ringing)

04:07.009 --> 04:08.676
Why would I want to do
a duet with you?

04:08.728 --> 04:09.611
We can't stand each other.

04:09.678 --> 04:10.729
Look, Wheezy, I realize

04:10.813 --> 04:12.346
I've tried to punch you
a couple times,

04:12.398 --> 04:13.615
and sometimes, when
you're not looking,

04:13.682 --> 04:15.366
I puweird things
in your food.

04:15.451 --> 04:17.067
But it's a new year,
and you and I

04:17.153 --> 04:18.319
are the best singers
at this school.

04:18.370 --> 04:19.571
I don't get what
the big deal is,

04:19.654 --> 04:21.322
it's just a free trip
to Breadstix.

04:21.373 --> 04:24.793
<i>Um, I'm sorry, have you
been to Breadstix?</i>

04:24.860 --> 04:28.663
They are legally forbidden to
stop bringing you breadsticks.

04:28.714 --> 04:30.531
One time I brought
a wheelbarrow,

04:30.583 --> 04:31.633
and when the mager tried

04:31.700 --> 04:33.068
to stop me from
filling it up,

04:33.135 --> 04:34.319
I calleded the corporae
office and got her fired.

04:34.403 --> 04:36.638
(sighs)

04:36.705 --> 04:39.474
Well, I guess our voices
do sorta go together.

04:39.525 --> 04:40.909
Mm-hmm, that's right, girl!

04:40.976 --> 04:42.961
So if we do a duet
together, we will be

04:43.028 --> 04:45.363
the undisputed top
bitches at this school.

04:47.616 --> 04:49.467
(bell ringing)

04:49.535 --> 04:50.752
You can't do this to him.

04:50.819 --> 04:51.652
You're over-reacting.

04:51.704 --> 04:53.088
If he sings with you,

04:53.155 --> 04:54.506
you're painting a
bull's-eye on his back.

04:54.590 --> 04:56.708
Once again, your closeted
homophobia seeps to the surface

04:56.792 --> 04:58.843
like the contents of
a cracked cesspool.

04:58.928 --> 05:00.361
Don't give me that.

05:00.429 --> 05:02.797
Look, I know I shouldn't have
used that word in your basement,

05:02.848 --> 05:04.332
but it's not like
you were innocent.

05:04.383 --> 05:06.217
I really like you, Kurt.

05:06.302 --> 05:07.835
But the fact
of the matter is,

05:07.887 --> 05:09.804
the way you were all
over me last year?

05:09.855 --> 05:12.524
if I did that to a girl, she'd
take out a restraining order.

05:12.608 --> 05:15.510
You have issues with me
being gay, I get it.

05:15.561 --> 05:16.728
No, actually, I don't.

05:16.812 --> 05:18.179
I have issues with
the fact that

05:18.230 --> 05:23.368
you don't understand
that no means no.

05:23.452 --> 05:24.819
I just want to
sing with him.

05:26.789 --> 05:29.824
Then you don't give
a damn about any of us.

05:29.875 --> 05:33.361
If he sings with you,
I guarantee, within a week,

05:33.412 --> 05:35.330
he'll take so much crap,

05:35.381 --> 05:37.165
he'll have to quit Glee Club.

05:38.584 --> 05:39.751
Your call, dude.

