07:18.183 --> 07:21.236
♪ Yeah! ♪

07:24.907 --> 07:26.207
We're totally going
to win this thing.

07:27.793 --> 07:28.643
I know.

07:32.581 --> 07:34.832
Wow. Don't be sad.

07:34.917 --> 07:37.001
I mean, Breadstix has these
vegan meatballs, they're...

07:37.086 --> 07:38.086
they're okay.

07:38.153 --> 07:39.671
I'm not really a nice person.

07:41.440 --> 07:42.924
I'm selfish.

07:47.162 --> 07:48.880
The fact is, is I'm
only really generous

07:48.964 --> 07:50.548
if there's something
in it for me.

07:50.633 --> 07:52.467
Yeah, but I
still like you.

07:52.518 --> 07:56.638
But you, you're so...
kind, a-and open.

07:58.841 --> 08:01.676
Well, it's made me
want to be a better person.

08:05.514 --> 08:06.898
We have to throw
the competition.

08:06.982 --> 08:08.750
I love Breadstix.

08:08.817 --> 08:11.018
No, i-i-if we wanna
win at Nationals,

08:11.070 --> 08:12.987
then Sam has to
win this contest.

08:13.055 --> 08:15.990
Okay? He has to feel
like he belongs and,

08:16.041 --> 08:17.325
and the team has
to believe in him.

08:17.376 --> 08:20.795
Wow, Rachel, I never
seen you like this.

08:20.863 --> 08:22.063
I'm kind of impressed.

08:22.131 --> 08:24.865
Well, like I said...

08:24.917 --> 08:26.584
you inspired me.

08:30.706 --> 08:32.056
But technically,
you're doing this

08:32.140 --> 08:33.775
because it'll help
us win Nationals,

08:33.842 --> 08:36.059
which means there's
something in it for you,

08:36.145 --> 08:38.563
so it doesn't really count
as you doing something nice.

08:38.630 --> 08:40.515
Okay, so I'm just gonna
ignore what you just said

08:40.566 --> 08:42.734
repeat what I said before:
we just have to find a way

08:42.818 --> 08:44.152
for me to lose
a singing competition

08:44.219 --> 08:45.570
so that the new kid
sticks around.

08:45.654 --> 08:46.604
Right.

08:50.658 --> 08:52.826
I don't want to do it.
We're duet partners--
you have to sing!

08:52.877 --> 08:54.261
<i>I don't even know
if I can sing.</i>

08:54.328 --> 08:56.496
Everyo knows I'm here
to do one thing: dance.

08:56.547 --> 08:58.298
You sing and I'll
dance around you;
you'll be fine.
No, no.

08:58.349 --> 09:00.017
We're singing together.

09:00.101 --> 09:01.501
We are gonna win that
dinner at Breadstix,

09:01.552 --> 09:03.020
and then we can finally
have a normal night out.

09:04.222 --> 09:05.722
Normal? What do you mean?

09:05.807 --> 09:07.357
We went out last night.

09:07.442 --> 09:09.309
For dim sum.
With your mom.

09:09.360 --> 09:12.062
All we ever do is get
dim sum with your mom!

09:12.146 --> 09:13.230
Here we go.

09:15.516 --> 09:16.667
Hi.

09:16.734 --> 09:19.303
So, I just want
you to know

09:19.370 --> 09:20.570
I'm really into you.

09:22.457 --> 09:23.657
Okay.

09:23.725 --> 09:25.075
Sorry, I'm...

09:25.159 --> 09:26.843
just a little confused.

09:26.928 --> 09:29.346
You've never even made
eye contact with me.

09:29.414 --> 09:32.299
I know. For a while
I thought you were a robot.

09:32.350 --> 09:34.134
<i>TINA:
I'm not saying that</i>

09:34.185 --> 09:35.335
steamed pork knuckles
aren't delicious.

09:35.403 --> 09:37.054
I'm just saying
that at Breadstix

09:37.138 --> 09:38.689
they have bottomless
salad bowls,

09:38.773 --> 09:41.308
they refill your salad
until you leave or pass out.

09:41.359 --> 09:43.143
You can get salad
at dim sum.

09:43.194 --> 09:44.511
My mom got salad
last night.

09:44.562 --> 09:45.862
There were chicken feet in it.

09:45.947 --> 09:48.365
It was a chicken
feet salad.

09:48.449 --> 09:50.283
All I want is
a normal salad

09:50.351 --> 09:52.352
that doesn't have
chicken feet in it!

09:52.403 --> 09:54.287
So, let me get this straight.

09:54.355 --> 09:57.074
You want to be my girlfriend

09:57.158 --> 10:00.877
because... you like
the idea of...

10:02.213 --> 10:03.830
...wheeling me around?

10:03.881 --> 10:07.134
I just really want
to get you in a stroller.

10:07.201 --> 10:08.385
<i>MIKE:
You're not listening to me.</i>

10:08.453 --> 10:09.970
You don't care
about my needs!

10:10.037 --> 10:11.221
Shh!

10:11.305 --> 10:13.140
We're fighting a lot.

10:14.709 --> 10:16.710
We should go to
Asian couples therapy.

10:16.761 --> 10:19.980
Why does the couples therapy
have to be Asian?

10:20.048 --> 10:22.215
So, I get to tell
everybody that we're dating?

10:22.266 --> 10:23.216
Yes.

10:23.267 --> 10:25.218
And I get a duet partner.

10:33.778 --> 10:35.395
I don't see the big deal.

10:35.446 --> 10:37.247
He e-mailed me, like,
60 MP3's of him singing,

10:37.331 --> 10:39.166
and I thought it was Faith Hill.

10:39.233 --> 10:40.784
The kid's good.

10:40.868 --> 10:43.069
Look, this isn't about
how good Kurt is.

10:45.506 --> 10:47.340
Being in Glee Club is like...

10:47.408 --> 10:49.426
it's like walking down
the double yellow lines

10:49.510 --> 10:50.727
of a highway.

10:50.795 --> 10:52.846
If you get just
a little off course

10:52.913 --> 10:54.264
you're gonna get crushed.

10:54.348 --> 10:55.766
I got to be honest.

10:55.850 --> 10:57.801
You're kind of confusing
my head right now.

10:57.885 --> 10:58.802
I mean,
do you remember

10:58.886 --> 11:00.187
what you said when

11:00.254 --> 11:01.722
you talked me
into joining Glee Club?

11:01.773 --> 11:02.773
(bell ringing)

11:02.857 --> 11:04.191
Nationals are
in New York City.

11:04.258 --> 11:06.276
Can you imagine
at it's going to be like

11:06.360 --> 11:08.278
coming home
with that first-place trophy?

11:08.362 --> 11:11.815
Most of the kids in this town
have never even seen the ocean.

11:11.899 --> 11:14.367
We'll be gods.

11:14.435 --> 11:16.603
I joined up
because I'm new here

11:16.654 --> 11:18.538
and you said
it would make me popular,

11:18.606 --> 11:20.440
and now you're telling me that
it's going to get me killed.

11:20.491 --> 11:22.492
Well, eventually you're going
get popular from it,

11:22.577 --> 11:23.994
believe me,
but until then,

11:24.078 --> 11:26.747
you got to lay low
a little bit,

11:26.798 --> 11:28.114
a-and singing a duet
with another dude

11:28.166 --> 11:29.583
is not laying low.

11:29.634 --> 11:32.385
I didn't realize you had
a problem with gay dudes.

11:32.453 --> 11:34.387
Look, I don't have
a problem with gay dudes.

11:34.455 --> 11:36.173
Everyone else does,
and we're living

11:36.257 --> 11:38.675
in their world,
and in their world,

11:38.760 --> 11:41.344
you singing a duet with Kurt
is a death sentence.

11:41.429 --> 11:43.597
(sighs)

11:43.648 --> 11:45.015
Well,

11:45.099 --> 11:46.483
I gave him my word.

11:48.352 --> 11:50.487
In my world, that's that.

11:54.242 --> 11:56.359
Boom!

11:56.444 --> 11:58.995
Welcome to Glee Club,
lady lips.

11:59.080 --> 12:00.914
(laughter)

12:06.120 --> 12:08.922
The blueberry flavor
is the worst,

12:08.989 --> 12:11.258
especially if it gets
down your pants.

12:11.325 --> 12:13.159
<i>I looked like a creature
out of Avatar down there</i>

12:13.211 --> 12:14.377
when I got Slushied.

12:15.763 --> 12:18.799
<i>I saw Avatar,
like, six times.</i>

12:20.268 --> 12:22.219
Oh.

12:22.303 --> 12:25.105
Anyway,
you'll get used to it.

12:26.274 --> 12:27.390
You're the head cheerleader.

12:27.475 --> 12:28.692
Why do you even bother?

12:28.776 --> 12:30.527
I mean, you don't
need Glee Club.

12:31.779 --> 12:36.316
I like to sing...
and the fact is

12:36.367 --> 12:37.868
those guys were
pretty cool to me

12:37.952 --> 12:39.536
